# Component Conventions

## File Organization

Each component lives in `src/components/<name>/` with these files:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `index.tsx` | Public entry — wires hook + view, sole export |
| `<name>.view.tsx` | Pure presentational component (receives all data as props) |
| `use-<name>.ts` | Hook with component state/logic |
| `<name>.logic.ts` | Pure functions (parsing, transforms, no React) |
| `<name>.content.ts` | Static strings, labels, constants |
| `*.test.ts(x)` | Colocated tests |

## React 19 Types

Import event **handler** types directly — never use the deprecated standalone event types (`FormEvent`, `ChangeEvent`, etc.) or `React.*` namespace:

```tsx
// Good
import type { SubmitEventHandler, ChangeEventHandler, KeyboardEventHandler } from "react";
onSubmit: SubmitEventHandler<HTMLFormElement>;

// Bad — deprecated
import type { FormEvent } from "react";
onSubmit: (e: React.FormEvent) => void;
```

## Styling

- All styles live in `tv()` slots — never use ID selectors or separate CSS rules for component elements.
- Browser resets (margin, padding, font inheritance) are handled by Tailwind Preflight — don't duplicate in slots.
- Mobile-first only: set mobile styles as base, override at `lg:` for desktop. Never use `max-*` variants.

## Exports

- Named exports only — no default exports.
- `index.tsx` re-exports the composed component as the public API.
